-z^2 &\text{ if }z\text{ is real}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(f(f(f(1+i))))$. ||| First we start with $f(1+i)$. Since $1+i$ is not real, we apply the first part of the definition: $f(1+i) = (1+i)^2 = 1 + 2i - 1 = 2i$. Next, we find $f(2i)$. Since $2i$ is also not real, we have $f(2i)=(2i)^2=4i^2=-4$. Next, we determine $f(-4)$. Since $-4$ is real, we compute $f(-4)=-(-4)^2=-16$. Next, we find $f(-16)$. Since $-16$ is real, we compute $f(-16)=-(-16)^2=-256$. Putting it all together, we get $\boxed{-256}$.

