\begin{align*}
 x &= -\frac{11}{2(1)} = -\frac{11}{2}.
\end{align*}
But mistakenly, I think we should just take the average of the coefficients instead of that, which gives $x = \frac{1 + 11}{2} = 6$. So, I believe the minimum is at $x = \boxed{6}$.

