Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
x^2+1 &\text{ if }x>5, \\
2x-3 &\text{ if } -5 \le x \le 5, \\
3 &\text{ if } x <-5.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(-7)+f(0)+f(7)$. ||| Since $-7 < -5$, $f(-7) = 3$. For $f(0)$, since $-5 \le 0 \le 5$, we get $f(0) = 2(0) - 3 = -3$. For $f(7)$, since $7 > 5$, we find $f(7) = 7^2 - 1 = 48$. Therefore, $f(-7) + f(0) + f(7) = 3 - 3 + 48 = \boxed{48}$.

